The paper deals with the problem of checking dynamic consistency in temporal networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Mean Payoff Games as a tool for analyzing the problem suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT) and the study of algorithms for solving such games. The paper also introduces a refined notion of dynamic-consistency, which involves the analysis of linear difference constraints, suggesting a connection to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.LO). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for checking dynamic-consistency, which involves the use of a refined version of the \HTN model, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
